channel.title: CVE Feed for IBM -- Client Application Access
channel.description: The latest CVEs for IBM -- Client Application Access

item.title: CVE-2018-1409|2024-08-05T03:59:39.073Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM Notes Diagnostics (IBM Client Application Access and IBM Notes) could allow a local user to execute commands on the system. By crafting a command line sent via the shared memory IPC, which could be tricked into executing an executable chosen by the attacker. IBM X-Force ID: 138708.

item.title: CVE-2017-1714|2024-08-05T13:39:32.165Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM Notes and Domino NSD 8.5 and 9.0 could allow an authenticated local user without administrative privileges to gain System privilege. IBM X-Force ID: 134633.

item.title: CVE-2017-1720|2024-08-05T13:39:32.300Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM Notes 8.5 and 9.0 could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary commands by carefully crafting a command line sent via the shared memory IPC. IBM X-Force ID: 134807.

item.title: CVE-2017-1711|2024-08-05T13:39:32.240Z -- ibm -- client%20application%20access
item.description: IBM iNotes 8.5 and 9.0 SUService can be misguided into running malicious code from a DLL masquerading as a windows DLL in the temp directory. IBM X-Force ID: 134532.
